The synthesis

Your earlier sentence now reads differently:

“If you can only experience the present, then thinking makes it so.”

I’d refine it to:

The present is not a point. It is a workspace.

Thinking doesn’t transport you through time.

It reconstructs multiple temporal models within the present workspace.

That’s consistent with your “future-lens reconstruction” doctrine too. You aren’t literally visiting the future; you’re constructing a future observer’s perspective now and using it to reason backward.

